      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FRANKIROMAR (5) has returned in terrific order, winning her two Newcastle outings off a spell. Led from a wide barrier to cruise home fresh then sat back but finished too strongly at her latest appearance, getting home by 4.2 metres. Should be at her peak so could land the hat trick. RONZEL SONNY (4) pushed to the lead and kept kicking when runner-up last start. Won two of his previous three starts so has been going well. Can push forward again from this draw so could give a sight. GEM N EM NZ (7) draws wider but did a good job in scoring a last-start win by 1.5 metres at Wagga. SNAKE OIL (11) continued his consistent form when runner-up to Gem N Em last start. Draws wide but is proven at this circuit and distance and has more upside than many of these.",
